==English==

===Etymology===
From ''Mansk'', Old Norse adjectival form of ''[[Mon]]'' "Man".

===Proper noun===
'''Manx''' (''plural:'' [[Manxes]])

# Manx [[Gaelic]], a [[Goidelic]] language spoken on the [[Isle of Man]]
# A [[w:Manx cat|Manx cat]]. <!--Shouldn't this be at [[manx]]? -->

